text: Nadarzyn is a village in Pruszków County, Masovian Voivodeship, in east- central Poland. It is the seat of the gmina (administrative district) called Gmina Nadarzyn. It lies approximately south of Pruszków and south-west of Warsaw. In 2007 the village had a population of 3,198. == Education == * Wyższa Szkoła Fundacji Kultury Informatycznej (College of the Information Culture Foundation) ==International relations== ===Twin towns – Sister cities=== Nadarzyn is twinned with * Mərdəkan, Azerbaijan ==External links== * Jewish Community in Nadarzyn on Virtual Shtetl ==References== Category:Villages in Pruszków County
